(21, 1, 1, 'Trapping atoms in a laser beam offers a new way to measure gravity', NULL, 'The technique can measure slight gravitational variations, which could help in mapping terrain', '<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">By watching how atoms behave when they&rsquo;re suspended in midair, rather than in free fall, physicists have come up with a new way to measure Earth&rsquo;s gravity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">Traditionally, scientists have measured gravity&rsquo;s influence on atoms by tracking how fast atoms tumble down tall chutes. Such experiments can help test Einstein&rsquo;s theory of gravity and&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/article/key-constants-new-measurement-casts-doubt-dark-photons\">precisely measure fundamental constants</a>&nbsp;(<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">SN: 4/12/18</em>). But the meters-long tubes used in free-fall experiments can be unwieldy and difficult to shield from environmental interference such as stray magnetic fields. With a new tabletop setup, physicists can gauge the strength of Earth&rsquo;s gravity by monitoring atoms suspended a couple millimeters in the air by laser light.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">This redesign, described in the Nov. 8&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Science</em>, could&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://science.sciencemag.org/cgi/doi/10.1126/science.aay6428\">better probe the gravitational forces exerted by small objects</a>. The technique also could be used to measure slight gravitational variations at different places in the world, which may help in mapping the seafloor or&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/article/extreme-measures\">finding oil and minerals underground</a>&nbsp;(<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">SN: 2/12/08</em>).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">Physicist Victoria Xu and colleagues at the University of California, Berkeley began by launching a cloud of cesium atoms into the air and using flashes of light to split each atom into a superposition state. In this weird quantum limbo, each atom exists in two places at once: one version of the atom hovering a few micrometers higher than the other. Xu&rsquo;s team then trapped these split cesium atoms in midair with light from a laser.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"wp-block-sciencenews-content-sidebar\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1rem; border: 1px solid #176cab; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1.45rem; line-height: 1.35714; vertical-align: baseline;\">Got you, atom</h4>\r\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-2-columns\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: flex; flex-wrap: nowrap; -webkit-box-pack: justify; justify-content: space-between;\">\r\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 25%; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; -webkit-box-flex: 1; width: 286.5px; max-width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; vertical-align: baseline;\">To measure gravity, physicists split atoms into a weird quantum state called superposition &mdash; where one version of the atom is slightly higher than the other (blue dots connected by vertical yellow bands in this illustration). The researchers trap these atoms in midair using laser light (horizontal blue bands). While held in the light, each version of a single atom behaves slightly differently, due to their different positions in Earth&rsquo;s gravitational field. Measuring those differences allows physicists to determine the strength of Earth&rsquo;s gravity at that location.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; flex: 1 1 auto; min-width: 25%; word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word; -webkit-box-flex: 1; width: 286.5px; max-width: calc(50% - 0.625rem);\">\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\"><img class=\"wp-image-958132\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%; display: block; height: auto; width: 286.5px;\" src=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/110619_MT_interferometer_inline_680.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<figcaption style=\"margin: 0.5rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.16667; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline-block;\"><span class=\"credit wp-credit-958132\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.625rem; line-height: 1.2; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; letter-spacing: 0.075em; text-transform: uppercase;\">SARAH DAVIS</span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">Measuring the strength of gravity with atoms that are held in place, rather than being tugged downward by a gravitational field, requires tapping into the&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/article/quantum-weirdness\">atoms&rsquo; wave-particle duality</a>&nbsp;(<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">SN: 11/5/10</em>). That quantum effect means that, much as light waves can act like particles called photons, atoms can act like waves. And for each cesium atom caught in superposition, the higher version of the atom wave undulates a little faster than its lower counterpart, due to the atoms&rsquo; slightly different positions in Earth&rsquo;s gravitational field. By tracking how fast the waviness of the two versions of an atom gets out of sync, physicists can calculate the strength of Earth&rsquo;s gravity at that spot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">&ldquo;Very impressive,&rdquo; says physicist Alan Jamison of MIT. To him, one big promise of the new technique is more controlled measurements. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s quite a challenge to work on these drop experiments, where you have a 10-meter-long tower,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;Magnetic fields are hard to shield, and the environment produces them all over the place &mdash; all the electrical systems in your building, and so forth. Working in a smaller volume makes it easier to avoid those environmental noises.&rdquo;&nbsp;</p>', 'posts/December2019/X29RzgrBSiM2dN14hifR.jpg', 'trapping-atoms-in-a-laser-beam-offers-a-new-way-to-measure-gravity', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2019-11-08 03:19:17', '2019-12-10 15:01:38', 8),
(22, 1, 2, 'The first artificial material that follows sunlight may upgrade solar panels', NULL, 'Dubbed SunBOTs, the devices can capture much more solar energy than stationary devices', '<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">As the sun moves across the sky,&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/article/internal-clock-helps-young-sunflowers-follow-sun\">sunflowers continually orient themselves</a>&nbsp;to soak up the most light (<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">SN: 8/4/16</em>). Now a type of human-made material can do that, too.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">This is the&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px 0px 1px; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: #176cab; text-decoration-line: none; transition: color 0.25s ease-in-out 0s; border-style: initial initial solid initial;\" href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41565-019-0562-3\">first artificial material capable of phototropism</a>, researchers report November 4 in&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">Nature Nanotechnology.&nbsp;</em>Stemlike cylinders of the material, dubbed SunBOTs, can maneuver to capture about 90 percent of available sunlight, even when the sun comes in at an oblique angle, materials scientist Ximin He of UCLA and her colleagues found. The technology could someday be used to optimize solar panels, desalinate water or move robots, the researchers say.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">Other scientists have made artificial substances that can bend toward light, but those materials stop arbitrarily. SunBOTs can self-regulate, moving into the optimal position needed to absorb the sun&rsquo;s rays, then making small adjustments to stay there as the sun shifts.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">That ability comes from a SunBOTs&rsquo; configuration: a stemlike polymer about 1 millimeter in diameter embedded with a nanomaterial that responds to light. The nanomaterial absorbs light and converts it into heat; the polymer shrinks in response to increased temperatures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">When He and colleagues trained a beam of light on one of these artificial stems, the illuminated side heated up and contracted. That caused its top to bend toward the light. The newly shaded underside of the stem then cooled, stopping the SunBOT&rsquo;s movement in a position best oriented to soak up the light. The process repeated as the angle of the light beam changed.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: inherit; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; height: auto; max-width: 100%; color: #31313b;\"><img class=\"wp-image-958028\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%; display: block; height: auto; width: 643px;\" src=\"https://www.sciencenews.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/110419_sb_sunbot_inline1_desktop.jpg\" alt=\"SunBOT\" />\r\n<figcaption style=\"margin: 0.5rem 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.16667; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline-block;\"><span class=\"caption wp-caption-958028\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.16667; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block;\">SunBOTs are designed to bend to meet different angles of a beam of light (arrows indicate the direction of incoming light), and can shift position as the light moves. That ability lets the devices capture more solar energy than stationary devices.</span><span class=\"credit wp-credit-958028\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 0.625rem; line-height: 1.2; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; letter-spacing: 0.075em; text-transform: uppercase;\">XIAOSHI QIAN, YUSEN ZHAO, YOUSIF ALSAID AND XIMIN HE</span></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">To build their initial SunBOTs, the researchers used gold nanoparticles and a hydrogel. But tests with other materials &mdash; such as carbon black nanoparticles and liquid crystalline polymers &mdash; revealed that the components could be mixed and matched.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; border: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; font-family: museo-sans, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #31313b;\">&ldquo;If we have this big repertoire of materials working with the same principle &hellip; scientists can use it in different environments for different applications,&rdquo; says Seung-Wuk Lee, a bioengineer at the University of California, Berkeley who was not involved in the study. For instance, hydrogel SunBOTs work in water, He&rsquo;s team found.</p>', 'posts/December2019/JALw5BCwksBWdEokkKvs.jpg', 'the-first-artificial-material-that-follows-sunlight-may-upgrade-solar-panels', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2019-11-08 03:20:17', '2019-12-10 13:05:59', 1),
(23, 1, 8, 'Mysterious bullet hole through Jesus Christ found on painting of The Last Supper', NULL, NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">A modern painting of&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The&nbsp;Last&nbsp;Supper&nbsp;</em>has been discovered with a bullet hole through the figure of&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/jesus-christ\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9190276-/topic/jesus-christ\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">Jesus Christ</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">In pictures shown exclusively by&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The Independent,&nbsp;</em>the damage is clearly seen on the three-and-a-half metre tall canvas by&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/lorna-may-wadsworth\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9190276-/topic/lorna-may-wadsworth\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">Lorna May Wadsworth</a>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"mpu0ArticleBody\" class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--mobile ad-wrapper--mpu0\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">The bullet hole was discovered as the painting was being prepared for display at the Graves Gallery in Sheffield. It had previously been on display behind the altar of a Gloucestershire country church for a decade.</p>\r\n<div class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--teads\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\">\r\n<div id=\"teads\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">The bullet hole was later confirmed by ballistics experts to have come from an air rifle.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">Wadsworth&nbsp;refashioned the biblical scene by modelling Jesus Christ on the Jamaican-born model&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/tafari-hinds\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9190276-/topic/tafari-hinds\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">Tafari Hinds</a>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"teads-amp-ad\" class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--mobile\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<figure class=\"inline-media align-none\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Sans\', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; color: #222222; will-change: opacity; opacity: 1; transition-duration: 1000ms; transition-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.8, 0, 0.6, 1);\"><img class=\"i-amphtml-fill-content i-amphtml-replaced-content\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: auto; padding: 0px !important; border: none !important; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; height: 0px; max-height: 100%; max-width: 100%; min-height: 100%; min-width: 100%; width: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; bottom: 0px; right: 0px;\" title=\"screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png\" src=\"https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/11/07/12/screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png\" sizes=\"calc(100%)\" srcset=\"https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/11/07/12/screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png?w660 1000w,\r\n              https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/11/07/12/screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png?w800 800w,\r\n              https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/11/07/12/screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png?w600 600w,\r\n              https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/11/07/12/screenshot-2019-11-07-at-12.52.56.png?w400 400w\" />\r\n<div class=\"caption-wrap\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 10px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: #f7f7f7; color: #88888a;\">\r\n<div class=\"caption-wrap\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 10px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: #f7f7f7; color: #88888a;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #888888;\">(The damage to Lorna May Wadsworth&rsquo;s painting of The Last Supper)</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">Commenting on the damage to her painting, the artist said in a statement: &ldquo;Initially, when I first saw the damage, I was so upset that I considered pulling the painting from the exhibition. However, it was also very important to me that whoever did the damage didn&rsquo;t &lsquo;win&rsquo;.&rdquo;</p>', 'posts/December2019/MuU4SCNYzh18GzTby8wY.jpg', 'mysterious-bullet-hole-through-jesus-christ-found-on-painting-of-the-last-supper', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2019-11-08 03:25:44', '2019-12-03 11:53:24', NULL),
(24, 1, 1, 'Keith Haring mural goes up for auction after being cut out of Catholic youth centre', NULL, NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">A&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/mural\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9162461-/topic/mural\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">mural</a>&nbsp;painted by&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/keith-haring\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9162461-/topic/keith-haring\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">Keith Haring</a>&nbsp;inside a Catholic youth centre is headed for&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/auction\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9162461-/topic/auction\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">auction</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">The mural, once located in Manhattan&rsquo;s Upper West Side, has been cut out and will be put on Bonhams&rsquo;&nbsp;auction block in November,&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\"><a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/18/arts/design/keith-haring-mural-auction.html?emc=rss&amp;partner=rss\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9162461-https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/18/arts/design/keith-haring-mural-auction.html?emc=rss&amp;partner=rss\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\">The New York Times</a>&nbsp;</em>reports.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">Haring, who died in 1990, painted it in the early Eighties inside a building housing Grace House, a Catholic youth organisation located on 108th Street between Broadway and Amsterdam Avenue, in the Morningside Heights neighbourhood, as previously noted by&nbsp;<a class=\"body-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ec1a2e;\" href=\"https://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20160801/morningside-heights/keith-haring-mural-may-be-at-risk-as-church-moves-evict-tenants/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" data-vars-item-name=\"BL-9162461-https://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20160801/morningside-heights/keith-haring-mural-may-be-at-risk-as-church-moves-evict-tenants/\" data-vars-event-id=\"c6\"><em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">DNAinfo</em></a>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"mpu0ArticleBody\" class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--mobile ad-wrapper--mpu0\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id=\"article-im-prompt\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">The mural begins with Haring&rsquo;s &ldquo;Radiant Baby&rdquo; figure, a symbol featuring a crawling infant surrounded by rays of light that is one of the most recognisable aspects of Haring&rsquo;s work.</p>\r\n<div class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--teads\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\">\r\n<div id=\"teads\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">Over the course of one evening, Haring added several other figures seemingly dancing up the stairs, covering two floors.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">The preservation of Haring&rsquo;s mural had become a topic of concern since speculation that the church would sell or lease the building emerged in 2016.</p>\r\n<div id=\"taboola-carousel-thumbnails\" class=\"ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--inline-taboola ad-wrapper--mobile\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: center; width: auto; color: #222222;\" data-sort-time=\"\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">Haring was involved in the Jesus Movement of the Seventies as a teenager. The experience later influenced his work and aesthetic.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"inline-block video\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 16px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: medium; line-height: inherit; font-family: \'Independent Sans\', sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; color: #222222;\"><iframe class=\"i-amphtml-fill-content\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: auto; padding: 0px; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%; display: block; height: 0px; max-height: 100%; min-height: 100%; min-width: 100%; width: 0px; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; bottom: 0px; right: 0px;\" src=\"https://players.brightcove.net/624246174001/SydS6Pxaf_default/index.html?videoId=5837728067001&amp;customParams=videoID%253D5837728067001%2526articleId%253D9162461%2526gs_channels%253Desi_safe%2Csafe_from_essence_blacklist%2Csafe_from_harvey_weinstein%2Cshadow9hu7_safe_from_nestle_blacklist%2Csafe_from_emirates_blacklist%2Cgv_safe%2Cgv_safe_adult%2Cgv_safe_arms%2Cgv_safe_crime%2Cgv_safe_death_injury%2Cgv_safe_download%2Cgv_safe_drugs%2Cgv_safe_hatespeech%2Cgv_safe_military%2Cgv_safe_obscenity%2Cgv_safe_terrorism%2Cgv_safe_tobacco%2Cpos_amazon_carnival_row_01%2Cpos_amazon_carnival_row_02%2Cpos_amazon_carnival_row_03%2Cpos_amazon_carnival_row_04%2Cpos_animal_cruelty%2Cpos_apple%2Cpos_asda_1%2Cpos_asda_10%2Cpos_asda_11%2Cpos_asda_12%2Cpos_asda_13%2Cpos_asda_14%2Cpos_asda_15%2Cpos_asda_2%2Cpos_asda_3%2Cpos_asda_4%2Cpos_asda_5%2Cpos_asda_6%2Cpos_asda_7%2Cpos_asda_8%2Cpos_asda_9%2Cpos_castroljuly%2Cpos_castroljulyvfive%2Cpos_castroljulyvfour%2Cpos_castroljulyvthree%2Cpos_castroljulyvtwo%2Cpos_google%2Cpos_inskin_safe%2Cpos_keyword_blacklist_microsoft%2Cpos_lner_block_v3%2Cpos_o2_oct19%2Cpos_santander_cycles%2Cpos_society_lgbt%2Cpos_terrorism_blacklist%2Cpos_ubs_tax_evasion%2Cpos_vitality_oct19%2Cpos_ysl%2Csafe_from_aegis_blacklist%2Csafe_from_asda%2Csafe_from_castrol%2Csafe_from_collective_landrover%2Csafe_from_emirates_crew_incident%2Csafe_from_emirates_pg%2Csafe_from_facebook_blacklist%2Csafe_from_fas_blacklist%2Csafe_from_halifax_misc_blacklist%2Csafe_from_instagram-mobkoi%2Csafe_from_mobkoi-celine%2Csafe_from_mobkoi_facebook_keyword%2Csafe_from_workdayh2%2Cgs_entertain%2Cgs_entertain_arts%2Cgs_society%2Cshadow9hu7_pos_loop_me%2Cgs_event_easter%2Cgs_society_religion%2Cneg_skycurfew_mobkoi_custom%2Cskyonecurfew_block%2Cind_big-experiences_sep16%2Cshadow9hu7_pos_keyword_blacklist_sky%2Cfamily_babies%2Cgs_shopping_misc%2Cshadow9hu7_pos_nestle_blacklist_v2%2Cgs_shopping%2526playertype%253Dclicktoplay%2526topictags%253Dkeithharing%2Cmural%2Cauction%26gdpr%3D0%26gdpr_consent%3Dnone&amp;customTargeting=%2F71347885%2F_main_independent%2Fin_arts_entertainment%2Fin_art%2Fin_news%2Fin_news_article&amp;playsinline=true\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>\r\n<div class=\"caption-wrap\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 10px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: #f7f7f7; color: #88888a;\">\r\n<div class=\"caption-wrap\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 10px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: #f7f7f7; color: #88888a;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"caption\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 6px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 14px; line-height: 18px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #888888;\">Support free-thinking journalism and attend Independent events</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 16px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 19px; line-height: 27px; font-family: \'Independent Serif\', serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: #222222;\">According to&nbsp;<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;\">The New York Times</em>, Haring ended up painting the Grace House mural after befriending some of the organisation members&rsquo; at the Paradise Garage nightclub, a historic LGBT+ site in SoHo.</p>', 'posts/December2019/8cXUShp7D7kfOZz7iX7p.jpg', 'keith-haring-mural-goes-up-for-auction-after-being-cut-out-of-catholic-youth-centre', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2019-11-08 03:27:43', '2019-12-10 17:06:09', 21);
