(27, 1, 11, 'Capital City of South Korea Has Finally Been Declared Dog Slaughter-Free Since Last Farmers Agreed to Switch Careers', NULL, NULL, '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">After one year of tireless advocacy work, the South Korean city of Seoul has finally been declared free of dog slaughter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">Seoul&rsquo;s last three dog meat shops have agreed to end dog slaughter on-site, following over a year of campaigning from Seoul&rsquo;s Mayor Park Won-soon and the Seoul Metropolitan Government.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">The initiative has been welcomed by leading animal charity Humane Society International/Korea, which has been active in South Korea working with dog meat farmers to close farms, rescue dogs, and drive change.</p>\r\n<div class=\"td-a-rec td-a-rec-id-content_inlineleft  td_uid_33_5dc523704467d_rand td_block_template_1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; float: left; color: #222222; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;\">\r\n<div class=\"desktop-left\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; float: left; margin: 2px 20px 10px 2px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">HSI/Korea has so far rescued more than 1,800 dogs and closed 15 dog meat farms in South Korea since they began their work in the city back in 2015. Additionally, the organization has helped farmers to close down their dog meat farms and&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4db2ec; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/animal-activist-makes-historic-deal-meat-market-close-slaughterhouses/\">transition to alternative, more humane livelihoods</a>, as dog farmers are increasingly keen to exit the controversial trade due to societal shame, family pressure and decreasing profits.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bold;\">RELATED</span>:&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4db2ec; text-decoration-line: none;\" title=\"In Landmark Case, South Korean Court Rules That it is Illegal to Kill Dogs for Food\" href=\"https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/in-landmark-case-south-korean-court-rules-that-it-is-illegal-to-kill-dogs-for-food/\" rel=\"bookmark\">In Landmark Case, South Korean Court Rules That it is Illegal to Kill Dogs for Food</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">Dog meat consumption is also declining rapidly in South Korea, particularly among younger generations. A survey by Gallup Korea conducted in June 2018 shows that 70% of South Koreans say they will not eat dog meat in future. In July this year HSI/Korea assisted in the closure of South Korea&rsquo;s notorious Gupo dog meat market in Busan, following the&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; color: #4db2ec; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/south-korea-is-shutting-down-their-largest-dog-slaughterhouse-and-turning-it-into-a-public-park/\">closure the previous year of Taepyeong</a>, the largest dog slaughterhouses in the country in Seongnam.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">&ldquo;I am so happy to see Seoul&rsquo;s last remaining dog meat shops end dog slaughter,&rdquo; said Nara Kim, dog meat campaign manager for Humane Society International/Korea.&nbsp; &ldquo;Although these shops can still sell dog meat, it is nonetheless wonderful to see South Korea take one step further away from this dying industry that most Koreans want nothing to do with. It gives me hope that South Korea&rsquo;s future is dog meat-free.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: 26px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 26px; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;\">&ldquo;HSI/Korea will continue working with the government, and supporting farmers who no longer want to work in the dog meat trade, so that one day we will be able to celebrate the closure of South Korea&rsquo;s final dog slaughterhouse,&rdquo; she added.</p>\r\n<figure id=\"attachment_130530\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 6px auto 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; clear: both; color: #222222; font-family: Verdana, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; width: 696px;\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-130530\"><img class=\"size-large wp-image-130530 td-animation-stack-type0-2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; transition: opacity 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.39, 0.76, 0.51, 0.56) 0s; opacity: 0; margin-bottom: 0px; width: 696px; display: block;\" src=\"https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-1024x620.jpg\" sizes=\"(max-width: 696px) 100vw, 696px\" srcset=\"https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-1024x620.jpg 1024w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-326x197.jpg 326w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-768x465.jpg 768w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-696x421.jpg 696w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-1068x646.jpg 1068w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-694x420.jpg 694w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI-600x363.jpg 600w, https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Humane-Society-Rescuer-and-Rescued-Korean-Dog-Jean-Chung-HSI.jpg 1400w\" alt=\"\" width=\"696\" height=\"421\" />\r\n<figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-130530\" class=\"wp-caption-text\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-align: left; margin: 6px 0px 26px; font-size: 11px; font-style: italic; line-height: 17px; color: #444444;\">Nara Kim, Campaign Manager of HSI Korea, interacts with Big Ben at a dog meat farm in Yeoju, South Korea, on Tuesday, September 24, 2019. The operation is part of HSIs efforts to fight the dog meat trade throughout Asia. In South Korea, the campaign includes working to raise awareness among Koreans about the plight of meat dogs being no different from the animals more and more of them are keeping as pets.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />Photo by Jean Chung / HSI</figcaption>\r\n</figure>', 'posts/December2019/30QBW1nNAUGwYuzX1XMZ.jpg', 'capital-city-of-south-korea-has-finally-been-declared-dog-slaughter-free-since-last-farmers-agreed-to-switch-careers', NULL, NULL, 'PUBLISHED', 1, '2019-11-08 03:35:27', '2019-12-10 17:37:28', 329);
